# Migration and terminology

When updating behavior, do **complete** migrations. Avoid leaving silent compatibility layers unless the team explicitly chooses them and documents why.

## 1) Single canonical path

- When a field, type, API, or route is replaced, remove old reads/writes in the same change set.
- Update persistence, UI labels, analytics, and docs together so one name owns the concept.

## 2) Terminology

- Search the repo for an existing term before introducing a new one.
- After a rename, one term should appear across code, docs, and tools.

## 3) Planning artifacts

Treat `.cursor/plans/**` or similar folders as **historical** planning output, not live contracts, unless your project says otherwise.

## 4) Done criteria

- No stale references in code paths touched by the change.
- No contradictory naming between implementation and canonical docs.
- No “temporary shim” comments unless explicitly requested and scoped.
